methods.getChunk:
**Incompatible overloads text - text from the first overload:**

Returns a chunk of data corresponding to the keys from the given OrderedKeys.

*Overload 1*  
  :param context: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.ChunkSource.GetContext) - A context containing all mutable/state related data used in retrieving the Chunk. In particular,
          the Context may be used to provide a Chunk data pool
  :param orderedKeys: (io.deephaven.db.v2.utils.OrderedKeys) - An OrderedKeys representing the keys to be fetched
  :return: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Chunk<? extends DefaultChunkSource.SupportsContiguousGet.ATTR>) A chunk of data corresponding to the keys from the given OrderedKeys
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param context: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.ChunkSource.GetContext) - A context containing all mutable/state related data used in retrieving the Chunk. In particular,
          the Context may be used to provide a Chunk data pool
  :param firstKey: (long) - The beginning key (inclusive) of the range to fetch in the chunk
  :param lastKey: (long) - The last key (inclusive) of the range to fetch in the chunk
  :return: io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Chunk<? extends DefaultChunkSource.SupportsContiguousGet.ATTR>

text:
An alternative set of defaults which may typically be used by ChunkSources which support a get method
 which only works for contiguous ranges. They should just implement getChunk(GetContext, long, long).
